title: Slow Cooker Southwest Chicken Recipe
directions: In a 3-qt. slow cooker, layer three-fourths each of the corn and beans and half of the salsa. Arrange chicken over salsa; top with remaining corn, beans and salsa. Cover and cook on low for 4-5 hours or until chicken is tender.
Shred chicken with two forks and return to the slow cooker; heat through. Top with the peppers, sour cream, cheese and onions if desired. Yield: 6 servings.
ingredients: 1 can (15-1/4 ounces) whole kernel corn, drained
1 can (15 ounces) black beans, rinsed and drained
4 boneless skinless chicken breast halves (5 ounces each)
Sweet red and yellow pepper strips, sour cream, shredded cheddar cheese and sliced green onions, optional
